data.title: Breakfast treat
data.text: I have eaten her before but it has been over a year. As always the eggs with shrimp etouffee was wonderful. I don't understand the Mexican dishes increasing in a New Orleans themed restaurant. One addition I would love to see is the New Orleans chicory coffee be available. I do not like the current coffee which tastes bitter and burnt to me but would love to be able to order chicory coffee to complete my experience. Otherwise the service and quality of food has always been good.

data.title: Great dinner!
data.text: AMAZING!!!  We went for my birthday dinner and it was delicious!  The BEST crawfish etoufee I've ever had!  Service was great and fast!

data.title: Excellent
data.text: We had an excellent dinner; the service was excellent and the food delicious. No complaints and would highly recommend.

data.title: Loved it
data.text: What a find! Excellent food and service. A comfortable casual feel with an upscale vibe. And to top it off live piano! Food with a flair of style with out straying too far from its Cajun roots. Soup lovers don't miss the seafood corn chowder WOW!

data.title: Wonderful Surprise
data.text: Visited this restaurant for the first time and what a surprise. The food was exceptionally good and so was service. The calamari entrée was cooked to perfection though I wasn't a fan of the tomato dip served - a simply spiced marinara would have sufficed over the greatly reduced tomato puree.  The seafood and corn chowder was delicious and packed with meat. The sausage gumbo was plentiful and tasty.  The fish special of the day (blackened cod on a bed of risotto in a sherry reduction sauce with shrimp and sautéed spinach) was very tasty. Spice was moderate - perfect since it didn't overpower the food itself. The flourless chocolate torte was delicious and when we got the leftovers home, we noticed that it had been powdered with a golden sheen.  Overall an excellent meal with attentive service.  Definitely has been put on my list for a return visit.

data.title: Mr and Mrs Blank
data.text:
Wonderful relaxing place to eat lunch ... music in the background, good service and great food 
Next time and there WILL be a next time we will do dinner

data.title: Nice change of pace
data.text: This place provides good, authentic gumbo in a great atmosphere.  The service is good, food interesting and tasty, and prices fair.  Very good selection of wines and liquors.  Can always go next door for an after dinner drink to connecting hotel.

data.title: Good food, great coffee, wonderful people
data.text: Always enjoy the breakfast buffet, great coffee and the pleasant and considerate nature of the employees.

data.title: Good Cajun
data.text: I was pleasantly surprised at the food, having eaten Cajun all over Louisiana.  One diner had a very finely chopped shrimp Cobb,I had a very good etouffe, and a third had a shrimp po boy with lots of shrimp.  Ask for bread and butter ... It's wonderful.  I would eat here again.

data.title: Would not recommend
data.text: This is really a sports bar...not a place to go for a pleasant dining experience .  It was very loud and very expensive for what you get.  It took at least 35 minutes to get our food and 2 of the entrees we ordered would have been pre prepared and the other was a hamburger ordered medium...no atmosphere other than sports bar type.  Would not recommend as there are a lot better choices in Colorado Springs .

owner_response.author: Shelby P, General Manager at Springs Orleans, responded to this review
owner_response.text: We are sorry to hear that your experience did not match up to our expectations. We have been working very hard on this as well as spacing out our seating times a bit so the kitchen is not to get overwhelmed. All of our items are made from scratch so there is a lot of care taken into each item. We do also have a piano player often and can change the environment. We are a lively New Orleans style restaurant with an open concept. Thank you for trying us and hopefully you give us another opportunity maybe on another evening or in the courtyard.
owner_response.title: Owner Response

data.title: Great Local Bar!
data.text: Stopped in for a beer and appetizer. Great atmosphere and friendly service. Definitely an upcoming downtown venue!

data.title: Loved it
data.text: Had a nice little lunch meeting here this past week. My first visit but for sure not my last. It is different than any other restaurant in the city. Had wonderful blackened chicken bites and beignets cooked to order. They were both fantastic. Service was on point and very friendly.

data.title: Best way to work
data.text: I work in the downtown area.  Had a meeting with a client who wanted to go to Springs Orleans. Wow, I am glad he suggested it. Phenomenal food, great service, and beautiful restaurant. I ordered the gumbo and ate every bite. Prices were reasonable and very unique menu. It's fantastic having a Cajun/ soul food in the springs. Will definitely go again.

data.title: My new favorite!
data.text: Food and staff were amazing. Such an amazing part of downtown. Will Definately recommend. I love the local flare in such a quaint area. Thank you!

data.title: Good but not great
data.text:
I had my birthday dinner here last week. The food was ok but not memorable. I had the monkfish special and I expected much more flavor out of a New Orleans themed restaurant. The fish was just plain bland. My wife enjoyed her meal of red beans and rice. As for the ambiance, it started out very pleasant but halfway through the meal the lights all were turned up. This is also not a place for soft conversation. 

I also just don't understand the TV / restaurant thing. When I eat out I definitely want to be disconnected from media. THis place had 2 or 3 large screen TVs above the bar area.

owner_response.author: Shelby P, General Manager at Springs Orleans, responded to this review
owner_response.text: Thank you for letting us know about your time at Springs Orleans. We are sorry to hear you did not enjoy the monkfish. We do rotate our fish special weekly so hopefully there is another opportunity to try something else. We do have T.V's but we also have piano players that do play as well as a wonderful courtyard to dine in that can feel like you have been transplanted to another time. Thank you for trying us and hopefully you give us another chance!
owner_response.title: Owner Response

data.title: I love this place!
data.text:
I came here to meet a group of friends and it was fantastic! The bartender was quick and on point with all our drinks. Not to mention very friendly. 

The food was delightful. Everything smells and tastes fresh and made to order. Very good cajun food. Real Orleans taste. 

The atmosphere is tasteful and happy. Nice music and decor to really make you feel like you're down south. Not to mention, beautiful artistry painted by whom I was told was a blind man. They were colorful and fascinating. A sight any person has to see for themselves.

On top of everything, the wait staff was nice and professional the entire time. The manager, whose name I believe was Kaylee, came up and greeted us too. A very pleasant and delicious experience at Springs Orleans!

data.title: Good place for lunch
data.text: This is a gem. Great decor. Loved the Brie Beignets appetizer and the Sherry Fettuccini with grilled vegetables.

data.title: It's all out of a box
data.text:
Great looking venue, friendly hoping to help staff. MISERABLE food. 

Had alleged shrimp and grits, instant grits with no attempt to improve and Costco quality very small shrimp, over sweet salad dressings, could go on but just know you will be happy not to attempt this weak try at Cajun food.

owner_response.author: Shelby P, General Manager at Springs Orleans, responded to this review
owner_response.text:
David,

We are sorry that the food was not up to your expectations. All of our sauces are made from scratch and we have several seafood items flown in from the coast . Our chef was classically trained in New Orleans as well as our ownership is from the area and personally approved each menu item. Hopefully you give us another opportunity to show you this as we try very hard to have everyone leave satisfied. I can be reached at 719-323-2000 if you would like to discuss further.
owner_response.title: Owner Response

data.title: Imagine Cajun in ColoSpr
data.text: Imagine our delight when these Cajuns found a restaurant in Colorado Springs.  As close to authentic as Coloradans can get and well worth the price. A lucky find.

data.title: Great menu, mediocre food
data.text:
We were delighted to find a Cajun restaurant in Colorado Springs, especially after we heard the chef was from New Orleans. The menu certainly sounds authentic, but we were disappointed in the food. I had shrimp and grits, my son had lobster pasta (not from the Cajun menu), and my husband had another Cajun dish. We also returned for breakfast to try the beignets. 

Overall, the food was just not very flavorful. The staff was very nice and the atmosphere is ok, but I would say not great on the food.

The one standout was an appetizer called Brie Beignets--like cheese puffs. They were really excellent.

owner_response.author: Shelby P, General Manager at Springs Orleans, responded to this review
owner_response.text: Thank you for letting us know about you recent dining experience with us. Thank you for pointing out the great staff. The Brie Beignets are also one of my favorites and a little bit of a spin on the original. We are sorry to hear the food did not have enough flavor for you. I hope you brought this up to the server as we make all dishes from scratch and can always correct it if it is not to your liking. I would love the opportunity to speak with you further to give us another chance. Thank you for coming in and hope to speak with you. 719-323-2000.
owner_response.title: Owner Response
